262
00:19:29,646 --> 00:19:32,396
I didn't get why he was so popular. It's fair enough.

263
00:19:32,396 --> 00:19:34,566
I totally agree.

264
00:19:34,566 --> 00:19:36,490
Hey.

265
00:19:36,490 --> 00:19:41,020
How do you live with all that jealousy and pride in your body?

266
00:19:41,570 --> 00:19:44,570
You're so annoying that I want to break your leg.

267
00:19:45,950 --> 00:19:49,996
Hey, they were badmouthing you like crazy over here.

268
00:19:49,996 --> 00:19:51,545
Call me over.

269
00:19:51,545 --> 00:19:53,976
I'll try to be a fair judge.

270
00:19:53,976 --> 00:19:56,336
Let me know next time.

271
00:19:56,336 --> 00:19:58,216
Sure.

272
00:19:58,216 --> 00:20:02,410
Those two really love badmouthing people.

273
00:20:03,840 --> 00:20:09,570
I could never tell if you were really okay or just pretending.

274
00:20:11,730 --> 00:20:15,610
I'd laugh when you said things that'd usually turn me away.

275
00:20:18,980 --> 00:20:25,510
It scared me when the idiot suddenly snapped like that.

276
00:20:26,700 --> 00:20:28,400
Tanaka-shi.

277
00:20:31,750 --> 00:20:34,360
Can you spare some of your time?

278
00:20:36,750 --> 00:20:38,250
Sure.

279
00:20:39,960 --> 00:20:45,310
I still don't get it. Why Amagi?

280
00:20:47,600 --> 00:20:50,010
Well, um...

281
00:20:51,600 --> 00:20:54,550
I'm sorry for lying.

282
00:20:55,940 --> 00:20:58,750
We're dating.

283
00:21:00,230 --> 00:21:02,860
You're so honest.

284
00:21:02,860 --> 00:21:05,530
I heard Takara told you everything.

285
00:21:05,530 --> 00:21:09,880
Yeah, I heard it from him.

286
00:21:10,790 --> 00:21:13,586
So let's stop this chat here.

287
00:21:13,586 --> 00:21:14,876
What?

288
00:21:14,876 --> 00:21:16,296
Bye.

289
00:21:16,296 --> 00:21:19,380
So you two didn't fight?

290
00:21:23,210 --> 00:21:26,670
Unfortunately, we're no longer friends.

291
00:22:09,570 --> 00:22:12,020
You're in a good mood.

292
00:22:12,020 --> 00:22:13,990
Did you talk to him?

293
00:22:13,990 --> 00:22:16,790
Of course, this is me you're talking.

294
00:22:18,130 --> 00:22:20,010
The conversation fell through, didn't it?

295
00:22:22,550 --> 00:22:24,900
As if, you idiot.

296
00:22:28,780 --> 00:22:30,380
That's good.

297
00:22:41,100 --> 00:22:44,380
Did you get to explain it to him?

298
00:22:44,380 --> 00:22:49,010
Not really. He didn't really give me a chance to.

299
00:22:49,010 --> 00:22:50,970
You freaked out, didn't you?

300
00:22:51,650 --> 00:22:53,820
A little.

301
00:22:53,820 --> 00:22:55,580
It's more than a little, right?

302
00:22:55,580 --> 00:22:57,180
I'm hungry.

303
00:22:57,850 --> 00:22:59,116
What should we do?

304
00:22:59,116 --> 00:23:01,050
I want to eat something.

305
00:23:01,730 --> 00:23:04,010
- And I'm paying?
- Yeah.
- I knew it.

306
